               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0157DDM">Dändera Dabra Mǝḥrat Mikāʾel / DDM</placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1750" notAfter="1850">Mid-18th – mid-19th cent.
                        (?)</origDate>
                  </origin>
               <provenance>The name of Walatta Ṣǝrḥa is written in a
                     secondary hand in blue pen in the lower margin (e.g., 9v, 23v, 26v) and over erasure in the supplication formulas (e.g.,
                        20v, 24v, 47v, 57r).
 The name of Walatta
                     Mar(yam), possibly the name of a former owner, is written in the main hand in
                     the supplication formula on 56v.</provenance></history>
